A couple good captures from tonight using the Rs 12-469 and optical microphone. One sounds like there are disbelievers or skeptics on the other side, same as here. The other is a testing message.
&quot;Think of anything and he may be recording us....Bullshit&quot;
&quot;Testing Frank....Nathan&quot;

Dave

--- vfp19968@... wrote:

From: &quot; RetroCom&quot; &lt;vfp19968@...&gt;
To: &lt;EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt;
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] RS 12-469 Recordings using the Optical Microphone
Date: Tue, 4 Dec 2007 15:01:23 -0800

Thanks Frank R. I get messages about heterodyning from time to time. The optical microphone system I use is ultra sensitive to low frequency vibrations. Perhaps they can use the &#39;Schuman resonance&#39; as a carrier.
A couple more captures from this session. This first one is very emotional.
&quot;I don&#39;t really wanna die&quot;

&quot;Give him more secrets&quot;

Dave


--- warrior18eii@... wrote:

From: Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] RS 12-469 Recordings using the Optical Microphone
Date: Tue, 4 Dec 2007 05:35:10 -0800 (PST)

Dave,

Good to see someone is working uninterrupted. I hear both those files and am excited that they mention heterodyning. I have been harping on that technique for years as a way they create voice sounds in 3 dimensional space.

Regards,

Frank R.

